about: Prathamesh is a full-stack software developer with over seven years of experience in various web domains, tech stacks, AI, and product development. He specializes in Node.js, React, and Python. Prathamesh aims to use the acquired skills in the software industry to effectively contribute to a company's business objectives and deliver innovative solutions.

experienceItems: Designed and developed an extension app for Workday to schedule interviews in a smart way.
Developed features, fixed issues, and enhanced the performance of the in-house product, Rooster. Converted several build systems to support TypeScript and migrated code accordingly.
Collaborated with the marketing and CRM teams to transition over 30 clients from Workday's default interview scheduling tool to Rooster for all interview scheduling.
Led a team of three junior developers, along with individual contributions.

Led a team of three to add features and improve the performance and scalability of the existing CMS dashboard. The dashboard was used to automatically generate checkout pages using Bitbucket pipelines.
Directed system testing and validation procedures and collaborated with customers and departments to solve technical issues, including software system design and maintenance.
Developed software systems using mathematical models to predict optimized pricing models.
Delivered the project to enable the generated checkout URLs from the dashboard to have massive traffic from various marketing channels. That was the company's primary monetization method.
Designed machine learning systems and applied algorithms to generate accurate predictions and resolve object detection problems.
Developed models to achieve business objectives and metrics to track progress. Managed available resources, such as hardware, data, and personnel, to ensure deadlines were met.
Delivered a complete POC that could identify celebrities on any webpage and show ads accordingly.
Designed and developed a web-based application that can connect to any CCTV infrastructure and add automated security rules using artificial intelligence.
Prepared UI for end-to-end analytics pipeline that was an admin's dashboard.
Scaled an initial POC product to get government projects, such as automatic real-time school attendance monitoring.
Contributed to various projects for top e-learning giants in the domain.
Developed products and features as per client requirements.
Improved in-house products to have high demand from top clients worldwide.

nodes.certificate: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming

nodes.title: Rooster
nodes.description: Rooster is an extension application for workday HCM (also works with several other HCMs in the market) to extend its ability to schedule interviews intelligently. Rooster has unique features such as auto-book, notifications, and automation. I proposed and implemented an automation feature that adds support for sending automated actions like sending calendar invitations, cancellations, and rescheduling.

nodes.title: ai-Sentinel
nodes.description:
AI-Sentinel is a web dashboard for AI-based smart surveillance security written with React and Node.js. It monitors the machine learning process developed in-house in C++ and shows results accordingly. You can configure cameras, connect existing DVRs, and configure various security rules.
My role was to design and develop front-end and backend flow, mentoring Jr. developers and splitting tasks among them. 

On the machine learning front, I worked on a few machine learning algorithms such as object detection, segmentation, etc.

nodes.title: Face Search App Lumos
nodes.description: Lumos is a cross-platform desktop application developed as a hobby project. It is built with Electron and React. Lumos allows users to search for faces in local photos by querying one or more faces to retrieve all images that contain the queried faces.

nodes.title: Annoy-Node
nodes.description:
Annoy-Node is a TypeScript typed binding for Annoy index (https://github.com/spotify/annoy). 

The Annoy library has out-of-the-box support for Python but not for JavaScript. The only existing binding library (https://www.npmjs.com/package/annoy) has no support for TypeScript and also lacks updated features; this made us write newer and better support for JavaScript and TypeScript using N-API.
